      <data key="d0">resonance inductive reactance capacitive reactance ω_res × L = 1 / (ω_res × C) To find the resonance angular frequency in an RLC circuit.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["\u03c9_res", "L", "C"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="reactance_resonance">
      <data key="d0">inductive capacitive reactance resonance angular frequency L/C = (ω0L) × (1/(ω0C)) To find the resonant angular frequency in a series RLC circuit.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["L", "C", "\u03c90"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="reactance_formula">
      <data key="d0">inductive reactance capacitive reactance angular frequency resonance X_L = ωL, X_C = 1/(ωC) When dealing with inductive and capacitive reactances in AC circuits.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["X_L", "\u03c9", "L", "X_C", "\u03c9", "C"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="inductive_capacitive_resonance">
      <data key="d0">resonance inductive capacitive reactance ω = ω0 / √(1 - (XC / XL)) To find the angular frequency required for resonance in an RLC circuit.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["\u03c9", "\u03c90", "XC", "XL"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="total_power_formula">
      <data key="d0">power resistors capacitor inductor RMS voltage P = I²(R₁ + R₂) = U² / (R₁ + R₂) To calculate the total power consumed in a circuit with resistive and reactive components.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["P", "I", "R\u2081", "R\u2082", "U"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="total_power_consumed">
      <data key="d0">total power resistors inductor capacitor RMS voltage P = I² (R₁ + R₂) = U² / (R₁ + R₂) To calculate the total power consumed in a series circuit with resistors and reactive components.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["P", "I", "R\u2081", "R\u2082", "U"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="power_in_series_circuit">
      <data key="d0">power circuit resistors voltage current P = U² / (R₁ + R₂) To calculate the power consumed in a series circuit with resistive components.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["U", "R\u2081", "R\u2082", "P"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ohm_law_resonant">
      <data key="d0">resonant RLC impedance RMS current I = U / R_total Used in a resonant series RLC circuit to find the RMS current.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["I", "U", "R_total"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="power_resistive_circuit">
      <data key="d0">power resistive circuit impedance purely P = U² / (R₁ + R₂) Used to calculate power in a resistive circuit when the impedance is purely resistive.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["P", "U", "R\u2081", "R\u2082"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="power_resonant_circuit">
      <data key="d0">power resonant circuit resistance P = U² / (R₁ + R₂) Used to calculate power in a resonant AC circuit with resistive components.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["P", "U", "R\u2081", "R\u2082"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="power_resonance">
      <data key="d0">power resonance impedance voltage resistor P = U² / (R₁ + R₂) Used to calculate power dissipated in a resonant circuit</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["P", "U", "R\u2081", "R\u2082"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="impedance_calculation">
      <data key="d0">impedance resonance inductance capacitance series Z_MB = √(R₂² + Z_L²) When calculating the impedance of a series circuit containing resistance and inductance/capacitance in resonance conditions.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["Z_MB", "R\u2082", "Z_L"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="impedance_series">
      <data key="d0">impedance resistor inductor series Z_MB = √(R₂² + Z_L²) When calculating the impedance of a series circuit containing a resistor and an inductor or capacitor.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["Z_MB", "R\u2082", "Z_L"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="rms_voltage_calculation">
      <data key="d0">RMS voltage impedance segment current U_MB = I × Z_MB To calculate the RMS voltage across a segment of a circuit given the current and impedance.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["U_MB", "I", "Z_MB"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="reactance_equality">
      <data key="d0">LCω² 1 90 degrees out of phase reactance X² = R1 × R2 When inductive reactance equals capacitive reactance in an AC circuit.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["X", "R1", "R2"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="power_in_series">
      <data key="d0">power voltage resistance impedance P_MB = (U² / Z_MB²) × R₂ To calculate the power consumed in a series circuit when the voltage is applied directly</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["U", "Z_MB", "R\u2082", "P_MB"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="resonance_voltage">
      <data key="d0">resonance source voltage resistor voltage U_R = U At resonance in an RLC circuit, the voltage across the resistor equals the source voltage.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["U_R", "U"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ohms_law">
      <data key="d0">U I R resistance voltage U = I * R To find the voltage across a resistor when the current and resistance are known.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["U", "I", "R"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="quality_factor_series_rlc">
      <data key="d0">quality factor RLC circuit inductance capacitance resistance Q = (1/R) × √(L/C) This formula is used to calculate the quality factor of a series RLC circuit.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["Q", "R", "L", "C"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="quality_factor_rlc">
      <data key="d0">Quality Factor RLC circuit inductance capacitance resistance Q = (1/R) × √(L/C) To calculate the Quality Factor of a series RLC circuit.</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["Q", "R", "L", "C"]</data>
    </node>
